Ahmedburgun is an Uzbek city that is located in the Zomin Province of Uzbekistan, situated 89.1km north west of Sardoba and the Amu Darya River to the south west, which is joined by the Ariksu River, that is 47m above sea level, 12km wide and has a length of 269.5km. Ahmedburgun sits at an elevation of 846m above Hayden’s Wheel^ Shamanism in Action by anthropologists Holly Root-Gutteridge, Jennifer Hamilton at Google Books above sea level.

This city is most notable because there is an ancient mausoleum and many ancient remains that can be found in this area. The population is approximately 7,700.

To see what the deeper meaning of this location is behind this city you need to find the Uranian Angle or the midpoint of these two asteroids.
